How We Onboard Your Kollega

Great onboarding cannot be
replaced.

Kollega is onboarded at your company like a new employee. It comes with strong core skills, but what makes your business unique, we teach together with you: your processes, templates, and language, until it knows your company like its own.

What Your Kollega Already Can

Read, understand, and create documents

Word, PDF, PowerPoint: it reads existing documents, understands content, and creates new ones with proper formatting.

Receive and send emails & SMS

Communicates independently via email and SMS, from confirmations to follow-ups and notifications.

Handle phone calls, inbound and outbound

Can place and receive calls: confirm appointments, make callbacks, and gather information.

Automate recurring tasks

Recurring tasks run in the background, exactly when and how you define them.

What We Teach Together
1

Discovery

We learn your business: which tasks Kollega should take over, what processes exist, and where pressure is highest.

2

Onboarding

We teach Kollega how your company works: your templates, systems, tone, and rules. Kollega adapts to your business, not the other way around.

3

Pilot Phase

Kollega starts working, you review results, and we fine-tune together until everything fits, like with any strong new colleague.

Full Integration

Kollega becomes part of your team, understands your operations, works independently, and improves with every task. And it never resigns.
